CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Consumer Protection – Consumer Contracts – Limitations Periods
3 FOR the purpose of prohibiting a consumer contract from setting a shorter time to bring an
4 action under or on the consumer contract than required by the law of the State;
5 excluding certain entities from the application of this Act; and generally relating to
6 consumer contracts.
7 BY adding to
8 Article – Commercial Law
9 Section 14–1328
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2013 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Commercial Law
15 14–1328.
16 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “CONSUMER CONTRACT” MEANS A CONTRACT
17 INVOLVING THE SALE, LEASE, OR PROVISION OF GOODS OR SERVICES THAT ARE FOR
18 PERSONAL, FAMILY, OR HOUSEHOLD PURPOSES.
19 (B) THIS SECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO:
